sec.p:
The clinical diagnosis of PLE was defined based on a combination of:


Clinical findings suggestive of an underlying disease known to be associated with PLE;

The demonstration of protein leakage from the gastrointestinal tract by either:


Technetium 99m-labelled (99m Tc) human serum albumin (HSA) scintigraphy; or

Fecal α1-antitrypsin clearance (AATC);




The response to appropriate treatment;

The exclusion of alternative causes of hypoalbuminemia.
